<bold><italic>G</italic></bold>
<bold><italic>roups: </italic></bold>During 6 months of follow-up, there were no sudden deaths in the observation group, with one case of cardiac death and two cases of re-admission due to aggravated heart failure (incidence rate: 3.90%). In the control group, there were two cases of sudden death, three cases of cardiac death and 6 cases of re-admission owing to aggravated heart failure (incidence rate: 14.29%). The incidence rate of cardiac events in the observation group was significantly lower than that of the control group (P&#x0003c;0.05) (<xref ref-type="table" rid="T3">Table-III</xref>).</p><p>
<bold><italic>Security and </italic></bold>
